"a.苦涩的；刻薄的 【英】 adj.苦涩的( sour, astringent)；刻薄的(sharp, bitter, or harsh) 【记】 acerb(尖，酸)+ic→ 尖酸的； 【同】 派生词: acerbity (n.苦涩, 刻薄) adj. 尖酸的, 苦涩的, 刻薄的(酸的或苦涩的味道、性格或语调) = sour = astringent = sharp = bitter = harsh 【例】The playwright allows an acerbic tone to pierce through otherwise arid or flowery prose 剧作家允许在枯燥或华丽的散文中插入刻薄的语调. 【记】acerbity[SAT](n 苦涩, 刻薄); acerb(adj 酸涩的, 刻薄的)读: a涩bic－苦涩的 【反】acerbity－saccharin(n 糖精) 【记】ace 扑克牌的A 尖，尖酸 + bitter 苦→尖酸苦涩；音：涩 + bitter 【相关】exacerbate 恶化，激怒 acerbic (adj.)  1865, originally, and usually, figurative: ""sour, harsh, severe"" (of speech, manners, etc.), from Latin acerbus ""harsh to the taste, sharp, bitter, sour"" (see acerbity) + -ic."
